ITALY: Italy crude imports up 4.1 pct in first half '96.Italy crude imports up 4.1 pct in first half '96.Italian imports of crude oil amounted to 30.2 million tonnes in the first six months of 1996 (equivalent to roughly 1.2 million barrels per day), up 4.1 percent from the same period in 1995, industry group Unione Petrolifera said in a statement.Libya accounted for 31.9 percent of imports, Iran 16.2 percent, Saudi Arabia 15 percent, the former Soviet Union 11.9 percent and Egypt 6.7 percent.-- Rome newsroom +396 6782501